Vice President Joe Biden called Iraqi Kurdistan Regional President Masoud Barzani to discuss recent political and military developments in Iraq. They discussed the calls made by Biden and President Obama with Prime Minister-designate Haider al-Abadi and encouraged Barzani to work closely with Abadi to build a diverse, inclusive government representative of all Iraqis. Biden also provided an update on the United States' humanitarian assistance to refugees on Sinjar Mountain and the efforts of the U.S. military to help Iraq security forces counter the threat posed by the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant. Barzani expressed his support for the appointment of Abadi and his willingness to work with him and other leaders to address Iraq's political, economic, and security challenges. Both leaders pledged to continue their regular communication.